import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core'; import { ActivatedRoute } from '@angular/router'; import { DataService } from '../data.service'; @Component({ selector: 'app-schedules', templateUrl: './schedules.component.html', styleUrls: ['./schedules.component.scss'] }) export class SchedulesComponent implements OnInit{ addedCourses:any[] = []; schedules:any[]=[]; constructor(private dataService: DataService, private route: ActivatedRoute) {} ngOnInit() { this.route.queryParams.subscribe(params => { if (params['addedCourses']) { // Parse the JSON string back to an array this.addedCourses = JSON.parse(params['addedCourses']); // Now, 'addedCourses' contains the array from the query parameter console.log(this.addedCourses); const url = 'http://localhost:3000/schedules?pageNo=1&limit=20'; // Prepare the request body with the addedCourses array const body = { addedCourses: this.addedCourses, }; // Send a POST request to the specified URL this.http.post(url, body).subscribe((data) => { // Handle the response data here and save it to this.schedules this.schedules = data; console.log('Response:', this.schedules); }); } }); } }
